https://medium.com/@develperbilalraza/setting-up-a-django-project-with-poetry-a-step-by-step-guide-25269a5869ea


Step by step

Make sure you have poetry
    poetry --version

Make sure you have Django
    pip3 install Django

Make sure you have rest_framework
    pip install djangorestframework
    pip install markdown       
    pip install django-filter 

Run 
    python3 manage.py runserver
    or poetry ...



Manual 

    pip3 install poetry
   

    django-admin startproject services 

    mkdir myApp && cd myApp
    poetry init
    poetry add Django
    
    poetry add djangorestframework


    poetry run python manage.py runserver
    poetry run python manage.py startapp EnergyResource

    poetry run python3 manage.py import_energy_data [filename]
    poetry run python3 manage.py clear_database
    


Case Test:

    poetry run python manage.py runserver
    
    Go to http://127.0.0.1:8000/energy/

    poetry run python3 manage.py import_energy_data [filename]

    Go to http://127.0.0.1:8000/energy/ or curl -X GET -H "Accept: application/json" http://127.0.0.1:8000/energy/
    
    Go to http://127.0.0.1:8000/energy/search?


    curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name": "Biomass place 1", "type": "biomass", "capacity": "175", "location": "Location I", "status": "active"}' http://127.0.0.1:8000/new/
    
    http://127.0.0.1:8000/energy/

    curl -X DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/close?eid=4c7a2745227fd92f5381d4dfce69468e5df1c348

     http://127.0.0.1:8000/energy/

